1
00:00:36,533 --> 00:00:38,600
<i>-Jessica?
-Where are you taking my father?</i>

2
00:00:38,733 --> 00:00:41,100
<i>- Where are you taking him?
- Let go of me!</i>

3
00:00:41,233 --> 00:00:42,533
<i> Dad!</i>

4
00:00:42,667 --> 00:00:43,767
<i> Mom, what's going on?</i>

5
00:00:43,900 --> 00:00:44,833
<i> It's Hazel!</i>

6
00:00:44,967 --> 00:00:46,267
<i> She took your father!</i>

7
00:00:46,400 --> 00:00:49,400
<i>Monster! You're a monster,
Hazel!</i>

8
00:00:49,533 --> 00:00:52,067
<i>Manuel, this is the start
of our new life.</i>

9
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:56,300
<i>I won't stop until you learn
to love me again, Manuel.</i>

10
00:00:56,433 --> 00:00:57,700
<i> Jessica, where are you?</i>

11
00:00:57,833 --> 00:00:59,200
<i> Where did you take dad?</i>

12
00:01:00,567 --> 00:01:01,933
<i> Where are you?</i>

13
00:01:05,700 --> 00:01:08,167
<i> Jessica, where are you guys?</i>

14
00:01:08,333 --> 00:01:09,700
<i> Hello?</i>

15
00:01:09,833 --> 00:01:10,633
<i> Mom.</i>

16
00:01:10,767 --> 00:01:11,767
<i> Mom.</i>

17
00:01:13,333 --> 00:01:15,833
<i> Do you believe me now?</i>

18
00:01:15,967 --> 00:01:17,267
<i> Jessica's in on it.</i>

19
00:01:17,400 --> 00:01:20,467
<i>If I can't have Manuel,
then no one will.</i>

20
00:01:20,600 --> 00:01:23,733
<i>So if you want your dad
to survive and recover...</i>

21
00:01:25,467 --> 00:01:26,433
<i> obey me.</i>

22
00:01:27,633 --> 00:01:29,600
<i> Or else...</i>

23
00:01:29,733 --> 00:01:31,533
<i>you will regret it
for the rest of your life.</i>

24
00:01:39,167 --> 00:01:41,367
<i> I have so many plans for us.</i>

25
00:01:41,533 --> 00:01:44,167
<i>Dreams and promises
that I will keep.</i>

26
00:01:44,300 --> 00:01:47,467
<i>I will do my best
to rebuild our family.</i>

27
00:01:47,600 --> 00:01:50,567
<i> When the kids forgive me,</i>

28
00:01:50,700 --> 00:01:54,967
<i>I'll bring back the joy,
laughter, and peace we once had.</i>

29
00:01:55,100 --> 00:01:56,100
Ma'am?

30
00:01:57,500 --> 00:02:00,500
- Yes?
- Miss Paz is here, Ma'am.

31
00:02:00,633 --> 00:02:02,767
- And Sir Abel.
- Sis.

32
00:02:02,900 --> 00:02:04,633
- Sis, I'm sorry.
- Felma.

33
00:02:07,667 --> 00:02:09,500
Sis...

34
00:02:09,633 --> 00:02:11,867
I tried to talk to Alice.

35
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:15,967
I acted nicely and told her...

36
00:02:16,133 --> 00:02:21,133
she could join us in the
business despite sabotaging FMP.

37
00:02:22,700 --> 00:02:24,467
But it didn't work, Sis.

38
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:28,067
It looks like she got
a scholarship

39
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:30,300
to a pretend-to-be-clueless
acting school.

40
00:02:32,533 --> 00:02:33,800
I'm sorry,

41
00:02:33,933 --> 00:02:35,200
it didn't work at all.

42
00:02:36,933 --> 00:02:39,067
I don't know what
to do anymore.

43
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:45,867
I can't keep Manuel off my mind.

44
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:49,033
I'm worried that...

45
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:51,367
his condition might get worse.

46
00:02:53,200 --> 00:02:55,333
Please don't get me wrong,

47
00:02:55,467 --> 00:02:58,367
but even though Hazel is cruel,
she's a good nurse.

48
00:02:58,500 --> 00:03:01,033
She'll take care of Manuel.

49
00:03:01,167 --> 00:03:02,933
Are you really siding
with that dwarf?

50
00:03:03,067 --> 00:03:04,233
No, Darling.

51
00:03:04,367 --> 00:03:07,767
I'm just telling the truth
so Felma can feel at ease.

52
00:03:07,900 --> 00:03:10,933
Let's wait for Manuel
to get better.

53
00:03:11,067 --> 00:03:13,533
Once he recovers,
he will come back to her.

54
00:03:13,667 --> 00:03:14,667
I'm sure of it.

55
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:17,667
But focus on FMP for now.

56
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:19,600
So you don't worry too much.

57
00:03:21,567 --> 00:03:25,000
We don't know
what Hazel's plan is.

58
00:03:25,133 --> 00:03:27,833
What if he takes Manuel away
for good?

59
00:03:31,833 --> 00:03:33,567
Just when...

60
00:03:33,700 --> 00:03:37,267
his dream of...

61
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:39,633
being forgiven by Andeng
was about to come true...

62
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:42,767
he was gone.

63
00:03:46,967 --> 00:03:48,633
I understand, Sis.

64
00:03:48,767 --> 00:03:50,567
I really get it.

65
00:03:52,733 --> 00:03:55,067
I also don't want
the kids to get hurt.

66
00:03:56,367 --> 00:04:00,267
I also don't want them to get
separated from their dad again.

67
00:04:02,900 --> 00:04:04,267
Go, Sis.

68
00:04:06,200 --> 00:04:07,933
Find Manuel.

69
00:04:13,167 --> 00:04:16,200
Abel and I will take care
of FMP. Okay?

70
00:04:22,867 --> 00:04:24,100
Thank you.

71
00:04:34,867 --> 00:04:38,167
What are you doing, Joel?
Why are you walking?

72
00:04:38,300 --> 00:04:39,667
What?

73
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:41,867
Why do you keep pacing around?

74
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:43,000
This is just short, slow walks.

75
00:04:43,133 --> 00:04:44,900
This will help
in the healing process.

76
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:48,133
What about you?

77
00:04:48,267 --> 00:04:50,200
Why are you here again?

78
00:04:50,333 --> 00:04:53,467
You're supposed
to be with your family.

79
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:56,333
I just brought food
I asked Didang to cook.

80
00:04:57,700 --> 00:04:59,900
And I can't leave you alone,
Joel.

81
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:03,533
I'm the reason
you're in that situation.

82
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,067
Andrea...

83
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:08,767
how many times
do I have to tell you

84
00:05:08,900 --> 00:05:11,467
that it's not your fault?

85
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:15,500
Sonny is the one who did wrong.
And he's already detained. Okay?

86
00:05:17,267 --> 00:05:19,067
How's your dad?

87
00:05:22,133 --> 00:05:25,233
We still don't have any leads.

88
00:05:26,833 --> 00:05:28,600
I'm such a terrible person,
Joel.

89
00:05:31,767 --> 00:05:33,533
I didn't forgive my dad
right away.

90
00:05:35,300 --> 00:05:36,567
I hurt him.

91
00:05:36,700 --> 00:05:38,633
And now that Hazel's keeping him
away from us,

92
00:05:38,767 --> 00:05:39,733
I can't do anything.

93
00:05:42,133 --> 00:05:45,667
Andrea, that's enough.

94
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:48,567
Does your family blame you?

95
00:05:50,133 --> 00:05:51,700
No.

96
00:05:51,833 --> 00:05:53,433
See...

97
00:05:53,567 --> 00:05:56,100
So, you shouldn't blame
yourself.

98
00:05:56,233 --> 00:05:57,967
I'm trying, Joel.

99
00:05:59,767 --> 00:06:00,967
But it's not easy.

100
00:06:01,100 --> 00:06:03,267
I feel guilty.

101
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:08,067
I can't bear
seeing my family crying.

102
00:06:08,233 --> 00:06:10,467
It's all my fault.

103
00:06:11,467 --> 00:06:12,733
Andrea,

104
00:06:12,867 --> 00:06:15,500
instead of blaming yourself,

105
00:06:15,633 --> 00:06:18,667
you should do something
to find your dad.

106
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:19,667
What about the van?

107
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:21,000
The plate number.

108
00:06:21,133 --> 00:06:23,233
You saw it. Do you remember?

109
00:06:30,133 --> 00:06:32,033
I only remember the numbers.

110
00:06:33,967 --> 00:06:35,767
43781.

111
00:06:36,667 --> 00:06:38,733
I panicked. I don't...

112
00:06:38,867 --> 00:06:40,967
I can't remember.

113
00:06:41,133 --> 00:06:43,900
I think I remember the...

114
00:06:44,033 --> 00:06:46,800
letters and numbers.

115
00:06:46,933 --> 00:06:49,233
NBF 4?

116
00:06:49,367 --> 00:06:51,167
So could the plate number be...

117
00:06:51,300 --> 00:06:54,767
NBF 43781?

118
00:06:54,900 --> 00:06:58,167
Do you know anyone from
the Road Transportation Agency?

119
00:06:58,300 --> 00:06:59,600
You could ask them to check.

120
00:07:00,733 --> 00:07:02,567
Mom's police friend.

121
00:07:02,700 --> 00:07:04,400
No, I got it.

122
00:07:11,533 --> 00:07:12,867
Jessica, pick up.

123
00:07:24,967 --> 00:07:26,733
Why is she rejecting my call?

124
00:07:28,500 --> 00:07:29,767
She's done it many times.

125
00:07:29,900 --> 00:07:31,233
Jeff, wait.

126
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:39,000
<i>Jessica, please let's forget
our issues for now.</i>

127
00:07:39,133 --> 00:07:40,567
<i> Please help us.</i>

128
00:07:40,700 --> 00:07:42,733
<i> At least for mom.</i>

129
00:07:42,867 --> 00:07:45,333
<i> Have mercy on her.</i>

130
00:07:45,467 --> 00:07:46,800
<i> She's so kind to you.</i>

131
00:07:46,933 --> 00:07:50,333
<i>She accepted you even though you
were the child of dad's affair.</i>

132
00:07:50,500 --> 00:07:53,033
<i>Is this what you do to her
in return?</i>

133
00:07:53,167 --> 00:07:56,300
<i> Please tell us where you are.</i>

134
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:12,767
You're so mean, Jessica!

135
00:08:12,900 --> 00:08:14,267
You're horrible!

136
00:08:15,167 --> 00:08:17,000
What's wrong, Coleen?

137
00:08:17,133 --> 00:08:19,267
She only replied
with a smiley emoji!

138
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:21,167
She's just playing with us.

139
00:08:34,767 --> 00:08:36,633
In your dreams!

140
00:08:41,467 --> 00:08:45,967
<i>Now tell me you don't take after
your demon and desperate mother.</i>

141
00:08:46,100 --> 00:08:51,567
<i>Maybe she never felt love
growing up and lacked care.</i>

142
00:08:51,700 --> 00:08:53,700
<i> That's why she's so cruel.</i>

143
00:09:04,133 --> 00:09:05,867
Hello, Jessica?

144
00:09:08,133 --> 00:09:09,467
<i> Jessica, hello!</i>

145
00:09:10,467 --> 00:09:13,367
Jessica, talk to me!
Where's dad?

146
00:09:13,500 --> 00:09:15,133
<i> Jessica, please!</i>

147
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:21,200
Manuel is only mine.

148
00:09:21,333 --> 00:09:22,633
Only mine.

149
00:09:24,233 --> 00:09:27,200
You will never see
your father again.

150
00:09:27,333 --> 00:09:29,200
You can't take him back from me.

151
00:09:31,433 --> 00:09:33,067
Manuel is mine.

152
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:34,933
You can't do anything.

153
00:09:43,667 --> 00:09:45,000
So annoying!

154
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:55,467
Hazel, are you serious?

155
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:57,933
You're going to lock up
my godchild, too?

156
00:09:58,067 --> 00:10:00,233
I gave her a chance to leave.

157
00:10:00,367 --> 00:10:01,967
But she stayed.

158
00:10:02,133 --> 00:10:02,967
Of course.

159
00:10:03,100 --> 00:10:04,800
Where will she go?

160
00:10:04,933 --> 00:10:07,533
I told her to go
to his dad's mistress.

161
00:10:07,667 --> 00:10:09,400
And tell her where we are.

162
00:10:10,900 --> 00:10:12,533
You don't mean that.

163
00:10:12,667 --> 00:10:17,500
Jessica just doesn't know
how to get out of that place.

164
00:10:18,633 --> 00:10:21,667
Wait, wait. Hazel,
enough with all this mess. Okay?

165
00:10:21,800 --> 00:10:23,200
You're dragging
the whole hospital down

166
00:10:23,333 --> 00:10:25,367
with your personal mess!

167
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:28,767
Did you know that Felma and her
children stormed in here?

168
00:10:28,900 --> 00:10:32,667
Please stop.
Stop piling on my stress!

169
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:34,000
Relax, Miles.

170
00:10:34,133 --> 00:10:35,800
I'm aware of what's going on.

171
00:10:35,967 --> 00:10:38,900
That's why I'm here,

172
00:10:39,033 --> 00:10:40,300
because I'm resigning,

173
00:10:40,433 --> 00:10:41,800
effective immediately.

174
00:10:43,667 --> 00:10:45,367
What?

175
00:10:45,500 --> 00:10:47,100
Are you serious?

176
00:10:48,167 --> 00:10:51,667
Have you thought about this?

177
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:53,033
What's gotten into you?

178
00:10:53,167 --> 00:10:54,600
How about your income?

179
00:10:54,733 --> 00:10:55,933
What will happen
to your husband?

180
00:10:56,067 --> 00:10:58,333
Manuel's medication
is expensive.

181
00:10:58,467 --> 00:11:00,700
Please, Miles. Stay out of this.

182
00:11:00,833 --> 00:11:02,167
I have friends in Canada.

183
00:11:02,300 --> 00:11:03,967
They owe me a lot.

184
00:11:04,100 --> 00:11:07,600
So anytime I need a financier,
they can't say no to me.

185
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,300
You're unbelievable.

186
00:11:11,700 --> 00:11:14,367
I'm only concerned about Manuel.

187
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:17,267
But if you don't care about it,

188
00:11:17,400 --> 00:11:18,767
there's nothing I can do.
Go ahead.

189
00:11:18,900 --> 00:11:20,733
Do what you want to do.

190
00:11:20,867 --> 00:11:22,733
But let me tell you this.

191
00:11:22,867 --> 00:11:24,967
Now that you've crossed
the line,

192
00:11:25,100 --> 00:11:27,333
you have nothing to return to.

193
00:11:27,467 --> 00:11:29,867
Okay, fine.

194
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:32,200
Just mind your own business
and shut up!

195
00:11:39,967 --> 00:11:43,600
So, you're leaving me alone
in Southcrest.

196
00:11:43,767 --> 00:11:45,133
I'm sorry, Alice.

197
00:11:46,333 --> 00:11:47,233
Family first.

198
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:50,367
I need to prioritize
my family.

199
00:11:52,567 --> 00:11:54,700
This is our chance...

200
00:11:54,833 --> 00:11:56,967
to be whole again.

201
00:11:58,267 --> 00:12:00,467
It's now or never.

202
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:03,267
Fine. I understand.

203
00:12:04,633 --> 00:12:08,500
Use my car for now.
You need it more than I do.

204
00:12:08,633 --> 00:12:09,567
Are you sure?

205
00:12:46,267 --> 00:12:47,633
Where did you take my father?

206
00:12:54,033 --> 00:12:55,000
Let go of me!

207
00:12:55,133 --> 00:12:57,100
I won't until you tell me
where you took dad!

208
00:12:57,233 --> 00:12:58,800
I said let go! Let go of me!

209
00:12:58,933 --> 00:13:00,200
What are you doing?

210
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:04,033
You think I won't fight you?

211
00:13:04,167 --> 00:13:05,500
- Go ahead!
- I'll take you on, Hazel!

212
00:13:05,633 --> 00:13:07,733
- Then do it! Fight me!
- Where did you take dad?

213
00:13:07,867 --> 00:13:09,800
Ouch!

214
00:13:09,933 --> 00:13:11,100
Help!

215
00:13:11,233 --> 00:13:12,467
Please help me!

216
00:13:12,600 --> 00:13:14,433
Sir, please help me!

217
00:13:14,567 --> 00:13:15,733
Hey!

218
00:13:15,867 --> 00:13:17,200
What are you doing to her?

219
00:13:17,333 --> 00:13:19,633
Please help me!

220
00:13:19,767 --> 00:13:21,633
He's harassing me!
He's hurting me!

221
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:23,900
- Please, help me!
- I didn't do anything to her!

222
00:13:24,033 --> 00:13:25,167
I'm not hurting her!

223
00:13:25,300 --> 00:13:26,700
- Help me!
- Guard!

224
00:13:26,833 --> 00:13:28,233
Guard?

225
00:13:28,367 --> 00:13:30,533
Please help me!

226
00:13:30,667 --> 00:13:32,167
What do you mean?
She's the one hurting me!

227
00:13:32,300 --> 00:13:33,367
I'm not hurting you!

228
00:13:33,500 --> 00:13:35,667
He tried to kill me!
He was harassing me.

229
00:13:35,800 --> 00:13:37,400
He was hurting me!
I'm glad someone came!

230
00:13:37,533 --> 00:13:39,233
What are you saying?
I didn't hurt her!

231
00:13:39,367 --> 00:13:40,300
She was actually the one
hurting me!

232
00:13:40,433 --> 00:13:41,767
She hit me with her bag.
She slapped me!

233
00:13:41,900 --> 00:13:43,133
Please call the police.

234
00:13:43,267 --> 00:13:44,800
- Sir, she's just pretending!
- You're a liar!

235
00:13:44,933 --> 00:13:47,433
She sat down out of nowhere.
And called for help!

236
00:13:47,567 --> 00:13:48,967
- Let go of me!
- No! You were hurting me!

237
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:50,533
You were trying to kill me!

238
00:13:50,667 --> 00:13:52,900
I will send you to jail!
You'll end up in jail!

239
00:13:57,500 --> 00:13:58,833
Why do you have
to bring me here?

240
00:13:58,967 --> 00:14:00,867
I didn't do anything wrong
to her.

241
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:02,300
I didn't hurt her.

242
00:14:02,433 --> 00:14:03,800
Sir, I just held her by the arm

243
00:14:03,933 --> 00:14:05,400
because I wanted to know
where my father was.

244
00:14:05,533 --> 00:14:06,900
But I didn't hurt her.

245
00:14:08,367 --> 00:14:09,367
Hey!

246
00:14:09,500 --> 00:14:11,867
Sir, he's the one causing
trouble at the hospital.

247
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:13,267
What trouble?

248
00:14:13,400 --> 00:14:16,067
Ma'am, do you want to file
your complaint now?

249
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:17,467
Let my lawyer handle it.

250
00:14:17,600 --> 00:14:19,333
I'll ask him to come here.

251
00:14:19,467 --> 00:14:21,300
Take care of him.

252
00:14:21,433 --> 00:14:23,933
- Put him inside the cell.
- Wait, wait! Hazel!

253
00:14:24,067 --> 00:14:25,267
Hazel!

254
00:14:25,400 --> 00:14:27,367
Sir, she's making up a story!
Why would you put me in here?

255
00:14:29,267 --> 00:14:30,933
She was the one hurting me!

256
00:14:31,067 --> 00:14:32,267
- Why would I go inside?
- Go on!

257
00:14:32,400 --> 00:14:33,800
Hold on! Let me explain!

258
00:14:33,933 --> 00:14:36,000
Hey! Hazel!

259
00:14:36,133 --> 00:14:38,233
Sir! Sir!
I didn't do anything wrong!

260
00:14:38,367 --> 00:14:42,500
I'm innocent! I didn't hurt her.
She hurt me!

261
00:14:42,633 --> 00:14:44,800
Don't put me in jail!

262
00:14:44,933 --> 00:14:46,400
Sir!

263
00:14:46,533 --> 00:14:48,067
Sir, don't lock me up here!

264
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:50,400
I didn't do anything wrong!

265
00:14:50,533 --> 00:14:52,333
I don't want to be here!

266
00:14:52,467 --> 00:14:55,267
She's the one who hurt me!
She hit me!

267
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:56,867
I didn't hurt her!

268
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:05,533
I hope you're doing okay.

269
00:15:08,100 --> 00:15:10,667
I hope you come back.

270
00:15:18,533 --> 00:15:21,067
Hello, Colonel Sarabia?

271
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:23,000
Yes. Do we have any updates

272
00:15:23,133 --> 00:15:25,767
on the plate number we're having
checked at the RTA?

273
00:15:25,900 --> 00:15:28,667
<i>I already asked my colleague
about it, Andrea.</i>

274
00:15:28,800 --> 00:15:31,167
<i> I'm just waiting for his call.</i>

275
00:15:31,300 --> 00:15:32,667
Okay.

276
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:34,067
Thank you. Thank you.

277
00:15:35,433 --> 00:15:36,700
Mom!

278
00:15:49,667 --> 00:15:50,767
Coleen?

279
00:15:53,267 --> 00:15:54,400
Andrea.

280
00:15:55,600 --> 00:15:58,200
I want to see dad.

281
00:15:59,067 --> 00:16:00,867
I miss him so much.

282
00:16:11,500 --> 00:16:12,833
I'm sorry, Sweetie.

283
00:16:15,200 --> 00:16:16,567
Sorry, because...

284
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:20,800
I got mad at you...

285
00:16:20,933 --> 00:16:23,100
for wanting to see dad.

286
00:16:26,033 --> 00:16:27,833
I wasn't ready yet at that time.

287
00:16:32,233 --> 00:16:33,533
I was furious.

288
00:16:35,733 --> 00:16:38,900
But now I know
what it feels like...

289
00:16:40,267 --> 00:16:41,567
wanting to see him...

290
00:16:44,033 --> 00:16:45,500
be with him...

291
00:16:49,233 --> 00:16:50,967
yet someone's standing
in the way.

292
00:16:53,167 --> 00:16:54,433
I'm sorry.

293
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:02,467
Mom, why? Is there a problem?
Is it dad?

294
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:03,533
No.

295
00:17:03,667 --> 00:17:05,700
Your older brother
is in the police station.

296
00:17:05,833 --> 00:17:07,467
Hazel had him detained.

297
00:17:07,600 --> 00:17:09,600
He said he'll be charged
with assault.

298
00:17:09,733 --> 00:17:10,933
What?

299
00:17:17,367 --> 00:17:18,133
Sir.

300
00:17:18,267 --> 00:17:20,067
Jeffrey has a visitor.

301
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:22,233
- Jeffrey, son.
- Mom.

302
00:17:22,367 --> 00:17:23,700
- Son!
- Mom.

303
00:17:23,833 --> 00:17:24,567
Son.

304
00:17:24,700 --> 00:17:26,667
- Mom.
- Son.

305
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:28,100
What did they do to you?

306
00:17:28,233 --> 00:17:29,433
Did they hurt you?

307
00:17:29,567 --> 00:17:30,767
No, Mom.

308
00:17:30,900 --> 00:17:33,100
But I don't want to be in here.

309
00:17:33,233 --> 00:17:34,467
I don't want to be in here.

310
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:38,067
-Please get me out of here, Mom.
-Atty. Yeban is on his way.

311
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:40,933
They're taking care
of your bail.

312
00:17:41,067 --> 00:17:43,167
I don't want to be here.
Get me out of here, please.

313
00:17:43,300 --> 00:17:46,133
I don't want to be here.
Get me out of here.

314
00:17:46,267 --> 00:17:47,667
Mom, please.

315
00:17:48,767 --> 00:17:50,000
Mom.

316
00:17:50,133 --> 00:17:52,833
<i>Mom, I don't want to be away
from you.</i>

317
00:17:52,967 --> 00:17:54,267
<i> Don't say yes to them.</i>

318
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:56,600
<i>Please, I'm begging you.
Help me.</i>

319
00:17:59,933 --> 00:18:02,433
Mom.

320
00:18:06,700 --> 00:18:08,933
Your dad's life is in my hands.

321
00:18:10,067 --> 00:18:11,933
<i> So don't make me mad.</i>

322
00:18:12,067 --> 00:18:13,633
<i> Because if I lose control...</i>

323
00:18:14,667 --> 00:18:17,467
<i>I might give him
the wrong medication.</i>

324
00:18:17,600 --> 00:18:21,300
<i>So if you want your dad
to survive and recover,</i>

325
00:18:21,467 --> 00:18:22,800
<i> obey me.</i>

326
00:18:23,733 --> 00:18:25,500
<i> Or else,</i>

327
00:18:25,633 --> 00:18:28,167
<i>you'll regret it
for the rest of your life.</i>

328
00:19:10,700 --> 00:19:11,700
Jessica.

329
00:19:13,267 --> 00:19:14,100
Dad.

330
00:19:16,700 --> 00:19:18,800
This isn't a hospital anymore.

331
00:19:18,933 --> 00:19:20,567
Dad, do you need anything?

332
00:19:20,700 --> 00:19:22,000
- Food?
- Where am I?

333
00:19:24,867 --> 00:19:27,000
We're at mom's old house.

334
00:19:28,600 --> 00:19:29,533
Why?

335
00:19:32,367 --> 00:19:33,800
Dad,

336
00:19:33,933 --> 00:19:36,233
it's the doctor's advice.

337
00:19:36,367 --> 00:19:38,933
They said you need...

338
00:19:39,067 --> 00:19:42,933
to be in a quiet place
to fully recuperate.

339
00:19:45,300 --> 00:19:46,600
Where's your Aunt Felma?

340
00:19:48,333 --> 00:19:50,100
Does she know?

341
00:19:51,600 --> 00:19:53,733
What about Jeffrey and Andrea?

342
00:19:55,233 --> 00:19:57,267
Coleen?

343
00:19:57,400 --> 00:19:59,733
Does she know where I am?

344
00:19:59,867 --> 00:20:00,700
Dad.

345
00:20:00,833 --> 00:20:02,733
Just calm down, Dad.

346
00:20:02,900 --> 00:20:03,800
Jessica.

347
00:20:05,133 --> 00:20:07,367
Jessica, answer me.

348
00:20:13,600 --> 00:20:15,800
Jessica, are you hiding
something from me?

349
00:20:15,933 --> 00:20:17,267
Are you lying?

350
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:23,100
Did your mom take me away
from my family?

351
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:26,767
Dad...

352
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:35,900
- Jeff!
- Jeffrey!

353
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:41,033
Good evening.

354
00:20:43,433 --> 00:20:45,367
Jeff, why did you go
after Hazel?

355
00:20:45,500 --> 00:20:47,033
I didn't.

356
00:20:47,167 --> 00:20:48,300
I don't hurt women.

357
00:20:48,433 --> 00:20:51,300
I don't want mom to smack me.
That woman put on an act.

358
00:20:51,433 --> 00:20:52,667
She made it appear
I was attacking her.

359
00:20:52,800 --> 00:20:56,200
You should've brought me
when you went after that demon.

360
00:20:56,333 --> 00:20:57,733
What would you do
if I brought you?

361
00:20:57,867 --> 00:20:59,967
I'll pull her tongue
until she confesses.

362
00:21:00,100 --> 00:21:01,300
That's gross, Sis.

363
00:21:01,433 --> 00:21:03,467
You'll have to touch her saliva.

364
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:05,200
What if she has rabies?

365
00:21:05,333 --> 00:21:06,900
Yuck.

366
00:21:07,033 --> 00:21:08,200
But, Jeffrey...

367
00:21:08,367 --> 00:21:11,233
if she's going to sue you,
that means we'll see her.

368
00:21:11,367 --> 00:21:12,533
It's our chance.

369
00:21:12,667 --> 00:21:14,400
We'll corner her.

370
00:21:14,533 --> 00:21:17,067
She won't file a case.

371
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:19,767
We went back
to the hospital's parking lot,

372
00:21:19,900 --> 00:21:21,233
and there was a CCTV.

373
00:21:22,600 --> 00:21:24,833
It showed
that Hazel's accusation

374
00:21:24,967 --> 00:21:28,367
against your brother is a lie.

375
00:21:28,500 --> 00:21:30,900
That woman is the worst.

376
00:21:31,033 --> 00:21:33,067
You should file a case
against her, Jeff.

377
00:21:35,200 --> 00:21:38,800
Attorney, what case
can we file against her?

378
00:21:38,933 --> 00:21:41,533
We can file a false complaint,

379
00:21:41,700 --> 00:21:45,067
unjust vexation, slander,

380
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:48,100
and malicious prosecution.

381
00:21:48,233 --> 00:21:50,367
Andrea, let's not do it.

382
00:21:50,500 --> 00:21:54,467
I don't want to waste
any time on that woman.

383
00:21:54,600 --> 00:21:55,933
And how can I file a case?

384
00:21:56,067 --> 00:21:59,367
We don't know which branch
of hell she's hiding from.

385
00:21:59,500 --> 00:22:01,200
We'll find them, Jeff.

386
00:22:02,500 --> 00:22:05,200
Colonel Sarabia already knows

387
00:22:05,333 --> 00:22:08,600
who owns the van that Hazel used
to get dad away.

388
00:22:17,367 --> 00:22:18,667
Manuel?

389
00:22:18,800 --> 00:22:20,100
You're awake?

390
00:22:21,133 --> 00:22:23,100
As I expected.

391
00:22:23,233 --> 00:22:25,033
You should really be up by now.

392
00:22:25,167 --> 00:22:27,767
My calculation of the
medicine's effect is correct.

393
00:22:27,900 --> 00:22:29,967
You see? I'm a great nurse.

394
00:22:30,100 --> 00:22:32,667
I can take good care
of your dad.

395
00:22:32,800 --> 00:22:34,333
Go downstairs and eat.

396
00:22:34,467 --> 00:22:35,667
I'll take care of your dad,
all right?

397
00:22:35,800 --> 00:22:37,333
Go on, Jessica.

398
00:22:42,500 --> 00:22:44,200
Manuel.

399
00:22:44,333 --> 00:22:45,367
Time to eat.

400
00:22:51,367 --> 00:22:53,100
Hazel, why did you
bring me here?

401
00:22:57,033 --> 00:22:58,500
To keep me away
from my family?

402
00:23:00,367 --> 00:23:02,100
What are you talking
about, Manuel?

403
00:23:03,100 --> 00:23:05,700
Focus on your recovery first.

404
00:23:08,300 --> 00:23:10,533
I want to talk to my family.

405
00:23:13,467 --> 00:23:15,600
Manuel, you just woke up.

406
00:23:15,733 --> 00:23:18,867
Eat first.
You need to recover. Here.

407
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:20,000
No, I'm not hungry.

408
00:23:21,067 --> 00:23:23,100
I want to talk to Felma.

409
00:23:24,167 --> 00:23:26,367
I want to talk to Felma.

410
00:23:29,933 --> 00:23:31,633
You're so unfair, Manuel.

411
00:23:32,967 --> 00:23:35,300
I'm the one with you,

412
00:23:35,433 --> 00:23:37,133
but you're looking
for someone else.

413
00:23:38,800 --> 00:23:40,300
You're hurting me.

414
00:23:42,400 --> 00:23:44,567
Hazel, you were the first one
to hurt me.

415
00:23:46,067 --> 00:23:47,167
I know.

416
00:23:49,033 --> 00:23:50,333
I don't deny it.

417
00:23:52,033 --> 00:23:53,733
So let me make it up to you.

418
00:23:55,467 --> 00:23:57,167
Let me take care of you.

419
00:23:59,700 --> 00:24:00,800
Manuel...

420
00:24:01,800 --> 00:24:03,033
I'm begging you.

421
00:24:04,533 --> 00:24:06,167
Eat first

422
00:24:06,300 --> 00:24:08,300
before worrying
about other people.

423
00:24:09,767 --> 00:24:12,167
All you've got in your stomach
is medicine.

424
00:24:12,300 --> 00:24:13,700
You need food.

425
00:24:14,900 --> 00:24:16,633
Just a few bites.

426
00:24:18,233 --> 00:24:19,300
Wait.

427
00:24:36,400 --> 00:24:39,000
Go on and eat.

428
00:24:41,300 --> 00:24:42,500
Okay, I'll eat.

429
00:24:45,200 --> 00:24:47,300
But after I eat,

430
00:24:47,433 --> 00:24:49,100
you have to answer
all my questions.

431
00:24:50,933 --> 00:24:54,767
And explain to me why you have
to take me away from my family.

432
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:01,533
Eat now.

433
00:25:06,600 --> 00:25:07,867
Eat now.

434
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:09,933
Can my children file a case
against Hazel

435
00:25:10,067 --> 00:25:11,733
for taking their father away
from them?

436
00:25:11,867 --> 00:25:14,100
Hazel is Manuel's legal wife.

437
00:25:14,233 --> 00:25:15,300
And under the Family Code,

438
00:25:15,433 --> 00:25:17,533
she has the authority to decide
on his care.

439
00:25:17,667 --> 00:25:20,600
The doctor advised me
to bring you somewhere quiet,

440
00:25:20,733 --> 00:25:21,800
away from the stress.

441
00:25:21,933 --> 00:25:23,667
That's why I brought you here
to the province.

442
00:25:23,800 --> 00:25:27,200
We suspect that Hazel forced him
to sign the discharge form.

443
00:25:27,333 --> 00:25:29,233
Yes. Or maybe they forged
his signature.

444
00:25:29,367 --> 00:25:31,133
It should be backed up
by solid evidence.

445
00:25:31,267 --> 00:25:33,100
We can't rely on mere guesses
or suspicions.

446
00:25:33,233 --> 00:25:34,500
Take your medicine.

447
00:25:34,633 --> 00:25:38,033
Why does it feel heavy?

448
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:40,433
Why do I feel sleepy?
I just woke up.

449
00:25:40,567 --> 00:25:42,467
Attorney, if we find them

450
00:25:42,600 --> 00:25:46,133
and prove that it wasn't
Manuel's wish to...

451
00:25:46,267 --> 00:25:47,367
release him from the hospital,

452
00:25:47,500 --> 00:25:48,733
what can we do?

453
00:25:48,867 --> 00:25:51,100
We can file a Petition
for Habeas Corpus.

454
00:25:51,233 --> 00:25:53,300
Meaning, the court
will order Hazel.

455
00:25:53,433 --> 00:25:57,367
She needs to prove that she's
not hiding Manuel unlawfully.

456
00:25:57,500 --> 00:25:59,833
I want you to see
that I've changed.

457
00:25:59,967 --> 00:26:01,200
My love for you.

458
00:26:01,333 --> 00:26:03,067
I will never see it, Hazel.

459
00:26:03,200 --> 00:26:04,433
Why? Is it because of Felma?

460
00:26:04,567 --> 00:26:05,867
Yes.
